'''Lucius Aelius Helvius Dionysius''' was a [[Roman Empire|Roman]] [[Politician|statesman]] who served as the [[Africa Province#Known governors of Roman Africa|Proconsul of Africa]] from 296 to 300 and as the ''[[Praefectus urbi]]'' from 301 to 302.<ref name="CoulstonDodge2000">{{cite book|author1=J. C. Coulston|author2=Hazel Dodge|title=Ancient Rome: the archaeology of the eternal city|year=2000|publisher=Oxford University School of Archaeology|location=Oxford|isbn=978-0-947816-54-4|page=136}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Ghisalberti|first=Carlo|title=Il Senato nella storia: Il Senato nell'età romana|year=1998|publisher=Istituto poligrafico e Zecca dello Stato|location=Roma|page=266}}</ref><ref name=Barnes85>"Proconsuls of Africa, 337-392", ''Phoenix'', '''39''' (1985), pp. 144-153</ref>

